As you will read, this boat is as nice as can be for a boat this year. I would proudly put it up against ANY 5 year old boat. It was kept inside a marina until I got it 3 years ago. Why am I selling it..........last year my mother in law with Ahlziemers came to live with us and we only got out on it 3 times. It’s too big for me to launch and retrieve by myself, so it’s for sale or trade. I don’t need $$$ so I would be happier trading it for a smaller center console or bass boat, or maybe a Harley.

I will trade for a smaller boat, a GUN COLLECTION, a Harley or $12,500.00 FIRM !!!

1998 Stingray 220CX

350 MAGNUM 300 horse power
Bravo One outdrive
141 hours, that’s right 141 hours !!!!!!! Will go up, I still use it.
Marina kept inside ‘till I acquired it 3 year’s ago.
This boat is WAY above average in condition and way low hours, way low. 
I traded a $14,000.00 Harley for this boat and right away put about $3,000.00 in it to make it as near perfect as it can be. It runs PERFECT, has never had a hiccup, the trailer is in perfect running order. The cuddy has a sink, single burner stove and porta potty. All cuddy cushions are as new ! Not a tear or anything anywhere.

Impeller replaced when I got the boat. 
I bought all new trailer tires when I got it.
Chain, anchor, and rode all new.
AM/FM CD new.
VHF ship to shore new.
Shakespeare 5225XT new.
Dual batteries, I bought 1 new and the other was 2 years old The list goes on.
I had the camper top windows replaced. Previous owner was quoted $1,500.00 alone for that but my guy cut me a little break on the price since he’s done work for me on my father in laws bass boat.

The first time out this year, a hub broke. Instead of just replacing it, I went ahead and had all 4 hubs replaced, all new COMPLETE brake assemblies replaced, everything, new hydraulic brake line from the front coupler clear back to the new assemblies. I don't play around. Also a solenoid went bad on my trim, so instead of replacing it, I had BOTH replaced and I even bought an extra to keep on the boat, just in case.

Almost a $1,000.00 in these repairs this week!!!

My new registration came in the mail yesterday, paid ‘till 2017.

When I see someone broke down on the water or the road, I always vow to myself that I will NOT be that guy. 
Rigged to fish off the swim platform, I didn’t allow fishing from inside the boat, I didn’t want it to smell or get bait dried up laying around, or hook rips in my interior. The interior doesn’t have a rip or anything wrong with it.
This 22’ Stingray is small enough to tow to any lake, anywhere, yet big enough to take offshore, the best of both worlds. With the 300 hp Mercruiser it will hit 60+ mph in near perfect conditions with 2 people and half tank of fuel, slight chop. That was GPS verified, NOT the in dash speedo!


How much am I asking.....$250,000.00, because I know you’ll want to talk me down on price, so let’s start there. I plan to end up with $12,500.00 in my pocket, a gun collection or a Harley.
 If your gun collection and/or Harley isn’t worth $12,500.00, you’ll need to add cash, to make up the difference. 


You will not find a nicer, cleaner low hour boat than this for the year. The boat looks near new, no rips, no tears, 141 hours, 350 magnum, Bravo 1 drive, new $400.00 cover,  no oil leaks.
I am anal with keeping this boat clean, perfect and maintained.

This boat is in tip top running condition at all times. The last thing I want is stranded on a broke down vessel !!!

Will also trade for Leer Jet, will need flying lessons.

The only thing this boat needs is the carpet cleaned and if I can get to it, I will have it done next week if it isn’t sold/traded before then.

THE PRICE IS FIRM. I WILL NOT TAKE A PENNY LESS !!!

This rifle started out as a standard Saiga Sporter and was quickly restored to it’s full AK glory.  All conversion holes were welded closed, and all of the metal was blasted, parkerized, and duracoated.

It features a genuine PK-23 red dot optic on a Tim Heffron Special Edition low mount.  It wears plum colored furniture from K-var.  Trigger is a Tapco G2 unit for legality and reliability.  Accepts all Mil-Spec magazines.

All of the donor parts such as the dust cover, rear sight, gas block, flash hider, gas tube, safety selector, cleaning rod, and trigger guard came from a numbers matching AK74 kit.  Muzzle brake was properly machined to upsize for the 7.62 projectile.

Barrel was shortened approximately 3 inches and finished off with an 11 degree target crown.  Muzzle brake has been permanently affixed per ATF regulations to maintain legal barrel length of 16 inches.

Includes 3 thirty round mags and a 75 round Romanian turn-key drum.

Looks great and shoots perfectly.  You will not be disappointed with this piece.
